result.execSummary:
The defendant Dominic D Wilkins was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: As to the amended count:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant sworn.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, jury instructions and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint. Judgment of conviction entered. Filed with the court:    Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Pretrial Incarceration Credit form, received and filed. Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 20.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 27, 2014 at 08:30 am.  Conditions of bail remain as set.

Defendant Dominic D Wilkins in court with attorney Adam Galaviz for Reyna I Morales.  James W Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  On State's motion court amended Count 3 to Criminal Damage to Property under 943.01(1) a Class A misdemeanor.  Defendant waived reading and pled not guilty.

Defendant Dominic D Wilkins not in court.  No other appearances.    Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until the next court date.  No bail is forfeited at this time.  Based on information provided to the court the case may have been miscalendared for this date.  Case adjourned to plea and sentencing to be heard with co-defendants' cases in Branch 20.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 21, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Dominic D Wilkins in court.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel was contacted and returned this clerk's call; she had miscalendared the case; requested same date of co-defendants.  Court ordered case adjourned for plea and sentencing before Branch 20 and that all terms and conditions of bail continue.  Defendant provided with his next court date by this clerk, which included the telephone number of his attorney.  Court instructed defendant to contact attorney.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 14, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Dominic D Wilkins in court with attorney Reyna I Morales.  Randy Sitzberger for James W Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Moroney, Branch 20.  Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty. Court ordered case adjourned for Scheduling Conference in Branch 20.  Scheduling conference scheduled for March 3, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with DEBORAH M. AND PROPERTY SHE OVERSEES AT 809 N BROADWAY, 53233.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.

Defendant Dominic D Wilkins in court with attorney Reyna I Morales.  Defendant Dominic D Wilkins in custody.  Sara B Lewis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.
